Key Match Events: Georges Mikautadze scored a penalty in the fourth minute of first-half stoppage time.
Patrik Schick equalized for Czechia in the 59th minute with a goal off his chest.
Saba Lobjanidze missed a crucial chance for Georgia at the end of the match.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was held at Hamburg's Volksparkstadion with an attendance of 46,524.
Khvicha Kvaratskhelia was a constant threat for Georgia.
Patrik Schick, joint top scorer with five goals at the last Euros, limped off after scoring.
